Conclusion¶

  1. Here, class 1, i.e. taken a loan from the bank is of more significance to the Bank and thus the TP for it is at the highest in the confusion matrix. Secondly, the ones which were predicted to be 1 but didnt subscribe for a loan, can be a like a buffer budget for the bank. Incase any other customer wants some more amount in their Loan.
  2. We were able to classify LoanOncard using Logistic Regression with an accuracy of
  3. We are able to classify LoanOnCard using Naive Bayes with an highest accuracy of 98% using undersampled data.
  4. Credit Card is highly correalted to LoanOnCard
  5. HighestSpend and FixedDepositACcount are also a deciding factor of the LoanOnCard
  6. Few features like InternetBanking, CustomerSince, HiddenScore are not having much relationship with LoanOnCard
  7. Standardization of data improves accuracy drastically.
  8. Normalization doesn't infact improve accuracy much.

Suggestions¶

  1. Many features like Security, HiddenScore dont have much significance to the class variable LoanOnCard
  2. Here, maybe some different variable like Occupation of the customer could have been better indicator of whether the customer will subscribe for a loan or not.
  3. Here, a person uses InternetBanking or not cannot determine whether they will subscribe for a Loan.
  4. The data is quite biased over LoanOnCard = 0, which may cause overfitting or underfitting due to sampling and we wont get the proper insights for the Bank.
  5. Quality thus could have been better of data by choosing proper attributes, Quantity by having some more records of LoanOnCard = 1.
